 Japan, where whale meat is part of the traditional cuisine,  reluctantly accepted a 1986 moratorium on commercial whaling by the  IWC.
 However, Japan's Fisheries Agency responded by saying that  foreign pressure would not force it into changing its whaling  policies.
 The 57-member IWC is scheduled to hold its annual meeting in Ulsan, South Korea, from May 27 to June 24.
 The Japanese plan is due to go before the International Whaling  Commission (IWC) when it meets in South Korea next month.